      "content": "It is wise to be mindful of your surroundings, but generalizations about entire neighborhoods are often inaccurate. Chicago is a vast city, and risk varies block by block, so instead of avoiding large areas, focus on researching specific blocks you plan to visit. Generally, sticking to well-trafficked commercial corridors even in those areas will provide more safety than walking through isolated blocks late at night. For a solo trip, prioritizing areas with constant activity is always a good strategy.",
