    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that, but i'm looking for more of an honest take. like, if i'm walking down a street and see a lot of certain demographics or if the neighborhood looks more 'urban' or lower income, is that a reliable indicator that I should be on high alert for crime? i'm just trying to be realistic about what the 'sketchy' areas actually look like so i know what to watch out for.",
