      "content": "While socioeconomic factors can sometimes correlate with different levels of urban intensity, relying solely on demographics or a neighborhood's appearance is not a reliable predictor of safety. Crime can occur in any area of a city, regardless of appearance. It is much more helpful to focus on situational awareness—being aware of your belongings and avoiding walking alone late at night in dimly lit areas—than trying to visually categorize \"safe\" versus \"sketchy\" blocks. Always trust your gut instinct when moving through an unfamiliar part of any city.",
